asses through.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heartofenglandway.org/the-route/about-the-route/|title=About the Route|website=www.heartofenglandway.org|accessdate=18 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Herefordshire Trail]] || {{convert|154|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Herefordshire]] || [[Ledbury]], Herefordshire || N/A || Circular route linking the market towns of [[Leominster]], [[Bromyard]], [[Ledbury]], [[Ross-on-Wye]] and [[Kington, Herefordshire|Kington]]. [[waymarking|Waymarks]] planned but not yet in place.\n|-\n|[[Hereward Way]] || {{convert|110|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[East Anglia]] || [[Oakham]] || [[East Harling]] ||  Through [[Thetford Forest]] linking the [[Viking Way]] and the [[Peddars Way]] long-distance footpaths. The [[Stamford, Lincolnshire|Stamford]] to [[Peterborough]] section is not fully [[waymarking|waymarked]], but walkers travelling between those two places can follow the [[waymarking|waymarked]] [[Torpel Way]].\n|-\n|[[Hertfordshire Way]] || {{convert|194|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Hertfordshire]] || N/A || N/A || Circular walk in open countryside, although some parts are within 20 miles of London. Passes through the county town of [[Hertford]] and the towns of [[Royston, Hertfordshire|Royston]] and [[Bishop\u2019s Stortford]]. \n|-\n|[[Icknield Way Path]] || {{convert|110|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Buckinghamshire]], [[Cambridgeshire]], [[Norfolk]] || [[Ivinghoe Beacon]] || [[Knettishall Heath]] || [[Prehistoric]] pathways passing through many sites of archaeological remains.<ref>[http://www.icknieldwaypath.co.uk/ Icknield Way Path]</ref>\n|-\n|[[Jack Mytton Way]] || {{convert|93|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Shropshire]] || [[Bridgnorth]] || [[Much Wenlock]] || Runs through the [[Shropshire Hills]] and the [[Clee Hills]] including parts of [[Wenlock Edge]].\n|-\n|[[Jurassic Way]] || {{convert|88|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[The Midlands]] || [[Banbury]], Oxfordshire || [[Stamford, Lin