daries of the ancient [[wapentake]] of The Ainsty.\n|-\n| [[Bront\u00eb Way]] || {{convert|43|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || West Yorkshire and [[Lancashire]] || [[Birstall, West Yorkshire|Birstall]] || [[Padiham]] || Links places that have strong associations with the writings of the [[Bront\u00eb family]].\n|-\n|[[Bullock Smithy Hike]] || {{convert|56|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || Central England, Northern England and the [[Peak District]] || [[Hazel Grove]], [[Greater Manchester]] || N/A || Circular challenge walk with over {{convert|7,000|ft|m}} of accent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ldwa.org.uk/challenge_events/show_event.php?event_id=12873|title=The New Bullock Smithy Hike|website=LDWA}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Bullock Smithy Hike]] || {{convert|40|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Lancashire]] || N/A || N/A || Circular route around [[Burnley]], covering a range of terrain from canal towpaths to open moorland.\n|-\n|[[Calderdale Way]] || {{convert|50|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Calderdale]], [[West Yorkshire]] || [[Greetland]] || N/A || Ccircular route devised in the 1970s.\n|-\n|[[Centenary Way]] || {{convert|83|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || Yorkshire || [[York]] || [[Filey Brigg]] || Runs across the [[Howardian Hills]] and [[Yorkshire Wolds]] via [[Castle Howard]] and [[Wharram Percy]].\n|-\n|[[Cistercian Way (England)|Cistercian Way]] || {{convert|24|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Cumbria]] || [[Grange-over-Sands]] || [[Roa Island]] || Partially waymarked, no longer recognised by [[Ordnance Survey]] or the [[Cumbria County Council]].<ref>[http://www.ldwa.org.uk/ldp/members/show_path.php?menu_type=S&path_id=81 LDWA webpage] Retrieved 26 February 2012</ref>\n|-\n|[[Coast to Coast Walk]] || {{convert|192|mi|km|0|disp=table|sortable=on}} || [[Cumbria]] and [[North Yorkshire]] || [[St. Bees]] || [[Robin Hood's Bay]] || Passes through three [[national parks of England and Wales|national parks]]: the [[Lake District]], the [[Yorkshir